#: data/civ2civ3/governments.ruleset:77
msgid ""
"* Buildings and technologies do not require any upkeep.\n"
"* Each worked tile that gives more than 2 Food, Shield, or Trade will suffer "
"a -1 penalty, unless the city working it is celebrating. Cities below size 3 "
"will not celebrate.\n"
"* Each city can support up to 2 units for free. Further units each cost 1 "
"shield per turn.\n"
"* Military units do not cause unhappiness even when deployed aggressively.\n"
"* Military units impose martial law. Up to 3 military units inside a city "
"will each force 1 unhappy citizen to become content.\n"
"* You have no control over national budget. Half of the trade income is "
"simply lost to your economy (less if you have luxury-promoting buildings), "
"and the remainder all goes to luxuries. Conventional corruption increases "
"with distance from the capital (half as fast with knowledge of The "
"Corporation).\n"
"* Base production waste is 30%. This increases with distance from the "
"capital (half as fast with knowledge of Trade)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/governments.ruleset:99 data/royale/governments.ruleset:111
#: data/sandbox/governments.ruleset:99
msgid "Tribal"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ2civ3/governments.ruleset:108 data/royale/governments.ruleset:120
#: data/sandbox/governments.ruleset:108
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
